version_description: In the prechorus, to generate interest, Am/G and Fmaj7 chords were added. But if you're a beginner or if they're too hard for you, you can just play G and F, respectively, instead. Also, near the end of some lines in the verses and the chorus, there are sometimes F and Dm chords quickly one after another. These are meant to be played offbeat in a syncopated manner. Just listen to the song, play along with it, and you'll get the hang of it.
